title.rendered: NBA All-Star voting results from 2023: Everything about Roasters Lists and Schedules

content.rendered:
NBA All-Star voting results from 2023: Ahead of this year’s celebrations, the NBA on TNT team will announce the runners and reserves for each conference. Once the player pool is complete, two All-Star Captains will select their teams just before the start of the All-Star game.Which players will make it? And which ones will get the unfortunate label of “snub”?Check out the full All-Star break down below.Which players will make it? And which ones will get the unlucky “snub” tag? (Read Also: NBA Player LeBron James near to break Kareem Abdul Jabbar’s record of 38000 points)

What is the NBA All-Star voting process?

Fan Vote accounts for 50 percent of the total votes to determine the starters for the NBA All-Star Game. Current players and members of the media split the other 50 percent.

Each ballot consists of two guards and three forward line players from each conference. NBA head coaches select reserves, and League Commissioner Adam Silver selects injured substitutes when necessary. The All-Star Captains then select their teams from the pool of eligible players (starters in the first round, reserves in the second Round).

Captains are chosen based on the players who receive the most fan votes in each conference. You don’t have to write because of your conference affiliation or position.

Let’s see the full All-Star breakdown below.

NBA All-Star voting results 2023

Eastern Conference starters (two guards, three frontcourts)

Captain: Giannis Antetokounmpo, Milwaukee Bucks

Position Player  Team                                                Player rank Fan rank            Mediarank Weighted score

G             Donovan Mitchell             Cavaliers             2              2                 1           1.75

G             Kyrie Irving         Nets      1              1              4              1.75

F         Giannis Antetokounmpo   Bucks    1              1              2              1.25

F              Jayson Tatum    Celtics   4             3              1              2.75

F              Kevin Durant      Nets      2              2              4              2.5

Jaylen Brown just missed out in the East backcourt, receiving a weighted score of 2.75. Joel Embiid just skipped in the East frontcourt, receiving a weighted score of 3.5.

Western Conference starters (two guards, three frontcourts)

Captain: LeBron James, Los Angeles Lakers

Position  Player Team     Player rank         Fan rank               Media rank         Weighted score

G             Stephen Curry   Warriors               2              1              2              1.5

G             Luka Doncic        Mavericks           1              2              1              1.5

F              LeBron James    Lakers   2              1              2              1.5

F              Zion Williamson                Pelicans                3              4              4              3.75

F              Nikola Jokic         Nuggets               1              2              1              1.5

Ja Morant (3.0 weighted score) and Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (4.0) was next up in the West backcourt. In the frontcourt, Anthony Davis (4.75) came up just short of other deserving candidates like Lauri Markkanen (5.75) and Domantas Sabonis (6.5).

Eastern Conference reserves (two guards, three frontcourts, two wild cards) – Eastern Conference reserves will be revealed on Thursday, Feb. 2.

Western Conference reserves (two guards, three frontcourts, two wild cards) – Western Conference reserves will be revealed on Thursday, Feb. 2.

2023 NBA All-Star Game Schedule

Fans in the US can catch this year’s All-Star Game events on Sling TV and now get HALF-OFF your first month! Stream Sling Orange for $20 in your first month to catch every regular season game on TNT, ESPN, and ABC. Subscribe to games on NBA TV Sling Orange and Sports Extra for $27.50 in his first month. Local regional lockdown restrictions apply.

Friday, February 17

  • Celebrity Game (7 p.m. ET)
  • Rising Stars Challenge (9 p.m. ET)

Saturday, February 18

  • HBCU Classic (4 p.m. ET)
  • Skills Challenge, 3-Point Contest, and Slam Dunk Contest (8 p.m. ET)

Sunday, February 19

  • 2023 NBA All-Star Game (8 p.m. ET)
